original: Corin, Göran Magnus, direktör, Göteborg, 7/9/78 i Gbg av grosshandl. C. G. C. o. Ulla Leffler. G. 25 m. Elsa Larsson. — Gen:ag. f. Sv:e f. Basels Försäkr :bol. mot brandskada sed. 09, verkst. dir. i Angf. A-B Gbg-Man-chester 11-15, grund, av Angf. A-B Thorsten, verkst. dir. där 16-22, medv. v. grund, av Försäkr. A-B Nornan, styr :led. där 18-24, verkst. dir. f. Fredr. Corin & Co. A-B i Gbg. Led. av Sv. försäkr :fören. o. Försäkr :-säMsk. i Gbg.
translated: Corin, Göran Magnus, Director, Gothenburg, born September 7, 1878 in Gothenburg, son of merchant C.G.C. and Ulla Leffler. Married in 1925 to Elsa Larsson. He was a general agent for the Swedish branch of Basels Försäkringsbolag against fire damage since 1909, managing director of Angf. A-B Gothenburg-Manchester from 1911-1915, founded Angf. A-B Thorsten and served as its managing director from 1916-1922, participated in the founding of Försäkr. A-B Nornan and was a board member from 1918-1924, and served as managing director for Fredr. Corin & Co. A-B in Gothenburg. He was a member of the Swedish Insurance Association and the Insurance Society in Gothenburg.
